main event: A UFO was sighted on November 15, 1965, near Eglin Air Force Base, Florida, evaluated as chemical trails from rocket firings.
interesting points: The object was described as possibly 13'3" x 3", long and flat or circular in shape., The sighting lasted for about 15 minutes around dusk., The observer had previous Air Force service and an avid interest in civil aviation., Other witnesses in Palm Harbor, Florida, supported the sighting, describing a massive object moving slowly., The document discussed the visibility of chemical trails across multiple states due to rocket activities.
sighted object: long and flat or circular object with blue-white or fluorescent color, resembling a neon light bulb
witness description: Mr. William R. Monckel, with prior Air Force service and two housewives from Palm Harbor
